                " \nRAILWAY SAFETY REGULATOR (RSR)\n ",
                " \n \nSAFETY INSPECTOR (CENTRAL REGION) (MIDRAND)\nReference Number: RSR-49\n \nDescription\nConduct a wide range of railway safety compliance activities, including the enforcement of safety compliance with the main intention of ensuring the continuous improvement of railway safety within the region. \n \nREQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS AND EXPERIENCE\nEngineering Degree/Diploma in any discipline NQF 6/7.\nRecognised Subject Matter Expert in any railway sub-system.\n5 years\u2019 experience in a railway safety background\n \nTHE FOLLOWING WILL PROVIDE AN ADDED ADVANTAGE\n Electrical Engineering Diploma/Degree NQF 6/7.\n5 years\u2019 experience in OHTE or Signalling\n \nKNOWLEDGE AND EXPERTISE\nSound knowledge of railway operations and railway sub-systems\nSound knowledge of relevant railway legislation and government policies relating to the rail industry\nIn-depth knowledge of the rail safety management system and applicable audit protocols, including the independent auditing and inspection thereof\nIn-depth knowledge of the local rail Industry and operators within his/her jurisdiction\nSound knowledge regarding NRSR Act and Railway Safety Standards (ISO/SABS)\nExcellent knowledge of regional railway operators/industry\nProject Management Principles and Approaches\n \nKEY RESULTS AREAS\nSwift response to railway occurrences when instructed to do so by the Principal Inspector or Regional Technical Manager.\nConduct railway safety audits and inspections as per the regional operational plan and in line with the RSR Compliance policies and procedures.\nDocument all audit and inspection findings, including recommendations in line with the RSR Compliance policies and procedures.\nEnforcement of compliance where non-compliances are detected in line with the NRSR Act and RSR Policies and procedures.\nSubmit accurate and complete reports to the Principal Inspector for approval.\nFollow through on all audits and inspection reports to ensure the appropriate and timely closure thereof.\nConduct site visits and inspections to ensure that the recommendations and/or non-compliances have been implemented by operators.\nEnsure that recommendations are correctly and accurately implemented to the extent that the identified risks are adequately mitigated.\nPromotion of railway safety compliance and awareness with all railway operators within the region.\n \nCLOSING DATE: 24 November 2023\n \nIf you are interested in applying for the above-mentioned positions, and for further details of the positions, please visit the RSR recruitment portal https://rsr.mcidirecthire.com/external/currentopportunities\nApplications must be supported by a motivational / application letter, comprehensive curriculum vitae, certified copies of qualifications and a certified copy of your identity document.\nApplications which do not comply with the abovementioned requirements, as well as those received late, will not be considered.\nThe RSR reserves the right to do vetting of references, credentials, criminal records (where applicable) and work experience of any candidate.\nONLY candidates with the qualifying criteria will have an opportunity to be screened and shortlisted for the process.\nThe shortlisted candidates must be willing to complete a competency assessment and medical assessment for inspectors in light of the inherent requirements of the job\nCorrespondence will be limited to shortlisted candidates only.\nIf you have not been contacted within a period of eight (8) weeks after the closing date of this advertisement, please accept that your application has been unsuccessful.\nIn line with the Employment Equity Plan of the Railway Safety Regulator, preference will be given to suitable candidates from the designated groups where applicable.\nThe RSR reserves the right not to fill any advertised position.\nThe processing of your personal information by the Railway Safety Regulator will be done in accordance with the POPI Act 4 of 2013.\nENQUIRIES: Please direct queries to Recruitment@rsr.org.za\n \nWork Level: Management\nJob Type: Permanent\nSalary: Market Related\nEE Position: No\nLocation: Midrand\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nEVENTS MANAGER (MIDRAND)\nReference Number: RSR-41\n \nDescription\nThis role is responsible for ensuring the successful planning, coordination, and execution of various events. The Events Manager will play a crucial role in enhancing the RSR's public image and maintaining strong relationships with stakeholders through memorable and well-executed events. This role requires a professional with a strong background in event management, excellent organisational skills, and a passion for delivering exceptional customer service.\n \nREQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS AND EXPERIENCE\nNQF 7 qualification in Communications/ Events Management or related field. \n5 years relevant experience.\n2 years in a management role.\n \nKNOWLEDGE AND EXPERTISE\nIn-depth knowledge of the use of various distribution channels, particularly electronic delivery, online and website.\nKnowledge of the composition and dynamics of the South African Railway industry.\nKnowledge of financial management and systems, including audit processes.\nKnowledge of government strategic planning and delivery processes.\nKnowledge of rail safety management systems.\nKnowledge of strategic planning and principles.\n \nKEY RESULTS AREAS\nEvent Planning and Conceptualization: Brainstorming and developing event ideas and themes.\nConducting market research and gathering information about the target audience.\nDeveloping strategies to promote the event and attract attendees.\nCoordinating with clients, sponsors, and partners.\nGathering feedback from attendees, sponsors, and stakeholders.\nCreating post-event reports, including successes and areas for improvement.\nConducting thorough assessments to understand the client's requirements.\nMaintaining open and transparent communication with clients.\nIdentifying potential sponsors by researching companies that align with the event or organization.\nEvaluating potential sponsors based on their brand image, target audience, and marketing objectives.\nClearly articulating what sponsors will gain from the partnership, including exposure, branding, and access to the target audience.\nNegotiating terms, benefits, and financial arrangements with potential sponsors.\nDrafting detailed sponsorship contracts outlining rights, responsibilities, and deliverables for both parties.\nConducting post-event financial evaluations to assess the financial performance of events in order to identify areas for improvement and to inform future event planning decisions.\nDeveloping strategies to generate revenue for events.\nReconciling the budget to compare actual expenses and revenues against the initial budget.\n \nCLOSING DATE: 24 November 2023\n \nIf you are interested in applying for the above-mentioned positions, and for further details of the positions, please  visit the RSR recruitment portal https://rsr.mcidirecthire.com/external/currentopportunities\nApplications must be supported by a motivational / application letter, comprehensive curriculum vitae, certified copies of qualifications and a certified copy of your identity document.\nApplications which do not comply with the abovementioned requirements, as well as those received late, will not be considered.\nThe RSR reserves the right to do vetting of references, credentials, criminal records (where applicable) and work experience of any candidate.\nONLY candidates with the qualifying criteria will have an opportunity to be screened and shortlisted for the process.\nThe shortlisted candidates must be willing to complete a competency assessment and medical assessment for inspectors in light of the inherent requirements of the job\nCorrespondence will be limited to shortlisted candidates only.\nIf you have not been contacted within a period of eight (8) weeks after the closing date of this advertisement, please accept that your application has been unsuccessful.\nIn line with the Employment Equity Policy of the Railway Safety Regulator, preference will be given to suitable candidates from the designated groups where applicable.\nThe RSR reserves the right not to fill any advertised position.\nThe processing of your personal information by the Railway Safety Regulator will be done in accordance with the POPI Act 4 of 2013.\nENQUIRIES: Please direct queries to Recruitment@rsr.org.za\n \nWork Level: Management\nJob Type: Permanent\nSalary: Market Related\nEE Position: No\nLocation: Midrand\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \n \nHEAD: RESEARCH AND TECHNICAL SKILLS DEVELOPMENT (MIDRAND)\nReference Number: RSR-42\n \nDescription\nProvide leadership and management in the development and implementation of research and skills development strategies to carry out the mandate of the Research and Technical Skills Development Department.  To support the RSR in achieving its vision, mission and strategic goals, and to ensure continuous safety improvement and mitigation of risks in the railway industry.\n \nREQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS AND EXPERIENCE\nEngineering Degree in any discipline or Transport related qualification \u2013 NQF 8\nRegistration as a Professional Engineer/Technologist\n10 Years\u2019 experience in the railway management or Engineering industry or operations environment\n3 years research within the railway industry\n3 years project management experience within the rail industry\n \nKNOWLEDGE AND EXPERTISE\nKnowledge of the Public Finance Management Act\nKnowledge of Auditing systems\nKnowledge of risk management issues\nIn-depth knowledge of legislation and government policies relating to rail industry\nKnowledge of rail safety management system\nIn-depth knowledge of rail industry\nWorking knowledge of communication & negotiations\nExpertise regarding safety legislation and standards (ISO/SABS)\nExcellent operator/industry knowledge\n \nKEY RESULTS AREAS\nProduce the annual business plan for the Department that is aligned to the RSR Strategy\nManaging and executing the approved departmental research and technical skills activities, resources as per the annual performance plan\nEnsure development of guidelines for all functions of the department\nOversee compliance to the CRM RA requirements for projects introduced to rail operations.\nLeading a team of specialists on all research projects planned and executed by the Division.\nPromoting and facilitating leading edge research across all disciplines in line with the goals of the RSR\nResponsible and accountable for all approved technical reviews of new technologies and new works\nEnforce compliance to standards with respect to design, construction and commissioning of new rolling stock, infrastructure, and technology.\nProvide regular feedback on the status of strategic rolling stock and modernisation project reviews\nManage the performance of staff in accordance with the Performance management system.\nProvide inputs in the development and implementation of a technical skills framework and strategy for the RSR.\nProvide inputs to ensure an effective and efficient memorandum of understanding (MOU) between RSR and organs of state and industry associations to ensure cooperation at the interface of operations by the inspectorate.\nManage the approved Budget as per the RSR objectives, project plans and schedules.\n \nCLOSING DATE: 24 November 2023\n \nIf you are interested in applying for the above-mentioned positions, and for further details of the positions, please  visit the RSR recruitment portal https://rsr.mcidirecthire.com/external/currentopportunities\nApplications must be supported by a motivational / application letter, comprehensive curriculum vitae, certified copies of qualifications and a certified copy of your identity document.\nApplications which do not comply with the abovementioned requirements, as well as those received late, will not be considered.\nThe RSR reserves the right to do vetting of references, credentials, criminal records (where applicable) and work experience of any candidate.\nONLY candidates with the qualifying criteria will have an opportunity to be screened and shortlisted for the process.\nThe shortlisted candidates must be willing to complete a competency assessment and medical assessment for inspectors in light of the inherent requirements of the job\nCorrespondence will be limited to shortlisted candidates only.\nIf you have not been contacted within a period of eight (8) weeks after the closing date of this advertisement, please accept that your application has been unsuccessful.\nIn line with the Employment Equity Policy of the Railway Safety Regulator, preference will be given to suitable candidates from the designated groups where applicable.\nThe RSR reserves the right not to fill any advertised position.\nThe processing of your personal information by the Railway Safety Regulator will be done in accordance with the POPI Act 4 of 2013.\nENQUIRIES: Please direct queries to Recruitment@rsr.org.za\n \nWork Level: Executive\nJob Type: Permanent\nSalary: Market Related\nEE Position: No\nLocation: Midrand\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nMANAGER: INTERNAL AUDIT (MIDRAND)\nReference Number: RSR-43\n \nDescription\nTo manage the execution of the internal audit plans with the aim to provide an impartial, accountable, transparent and efficient assurance and consulting audit results within the RSR. Furthermore, to contribute to the provision of value-adding internal audit service by adhering to a systematic and disciplined approach in evaluating the adequacy and effectiveness of risk management, control, and governance process. \n \nMINIMUM QUALIFICATION\nNQF Level 7 Internal Auditing or Accounting, B Tech: Internal Auditing, BComm. Degree (Auditing) or BComm Degree (Accounting) \nMinimum of 5 years Internal Auditing experience\n3 years Risk Management experience \n4 Years\u2019 experience in a managerial role \nInternal Audit Technician (IAT) \nProfessional Internal Auditor (PIA) \n \nKNOWLEDGE AND SKILLS\nKnowledge of transport legislation and  \nKnowledge of corporate governance principles \nKnowledge of Risk Management Frameworks \nKnowledge of Auditing Systems \nKnowledge  of RSR Act \nPublic Sector Risk Management Framework \nKnowledge of The Public Finance Management Act (PFMA),  Preferential Procurement Policy Framework Act (PPPFA) and Treasury Regulations \nApplicable Legislative and Regulatory Framework\n \nTHE FOLLOWING WILL PROVIDE FOR AN ADDED ADVANTAGE:\nQualification in ICT (in addition to the minimum qualification above)\nCertifications in the ICT environment\nExperience in managing ICT related audit projects\n \nKNOWLEDGE AND SKILLS\nKnowledge of transport legislation and  \nKnowledge of corporate governance principles \nKnowledge of Risk Management Frameworks \nKnowledge of Auditing Systems \nKnowledge  of RSR Act \nPublic Sector Risk Management Framework \nKnowledge of The Public Finance Management Act (PFMA),  Preferential Procurement Policy Framework Act (PPPFA) and Treasury Regulations \nApplicable Legislative and Regulatory Framework\n \n KEY RESULTS AREAS\nImplement the approved Audit plan \nManage internal audit scope and plan \nFollow-up on implementation of audit recommendations  \nProvide independent, objective assurance and consulting services \nImplement relevant frameworks, policies, plans for the provision of audit assurance and consulting services \nPerform and control the full audit cycle including risk management and control management over operations\u2019 effectiveness, financial reliability and compliance with all applicable directives and regulations \nCommunicate risks identified during execution of audit project\nEstablish and maintain effective relations with stakeholders \nManage subordinates by allocating work, assessing progress, coaching/ training and motivating \nProvide required training and development to staff to ensure optimal performance \n \nCLOSING DATE: 24 November 2023\n \nIf you are interested in applying for the above-mentioned positions, and for further details of the positions, please  visit the RSR recruitment portal https://rsr.mcidirecthire.com/external/currentopportunities\nApplications must be supported by a motivational / application letter, comprehensive curriculum vitae, certified copies of qualifications and a certified copy of your identity document.\nApplications which do not comply with the abovementioned requirements, as well as those received late, will not be considered.\nThe RSR reserves the right to do vetting of references, credentials, criminal records (where applicable) and work experience of any candidate.\nONLY candidates with the qualifying criteria will have an opportunity to be screened and shortlisted for the process.\nThe shortlisted candidates must be willing to complete a competency assessment and medical assessment for inspectors in light of the inherent requirements of the job\nCorrespondence will be limited to shortlisted candidates only.\nIf you have not been contacted within a period of eight (8) weeks after the closing date of this advertisement, please accept that your application has been unsuccessful.\nIn line with the Employment Equity Policy of the Railway Safety Regulator, preference will be given to suitable candidates from the designated groups where applicable.\nThe RSR reserves the right not to fill any advertised position.\nThe processing of your personal information by the Railway Safety Regulator will be done in accordance with the POPI Act 4 of 2013.\nENQUIRIES: Please direct queries to Recruitment@rsr.org.za\n \nWork Level: Management\nJob Type: Permanent\nSalary: Market Related\nEE Position: No\nLocation: Midrand\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
                "SAFETY INSPECTOR (EASTERN REGION) (DURBAN CENTRAL)\nReference Number: RSR-45\n \nDescription\nConduct a wide range of railway safety compliance activities, including the enforcement of safety compliance with the main intention of ensuring the continuous improvement of railway safety within the region. \n \nREQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS AND EXPERIENCE\nEngineering Degree/Diploma in any discipline NQF 6/7.\nRecognised Subject Matter Expert in any railway sub-system.\n5 years\u2019 experience in a railway safety background\n \nKNOWLEDGE AND EXPERTISE\nSound knowledge of railway operations and railway sub-systems\nSound knowledge of relevant railway legislation and government policies relating to the rail industry\nIn-depth knowledge of the rail safety management system and applicable audit protocols, including the independent auditing and inspection thereof\nIn-depth knowledge of the local rail Industry and operators within his/her jurisdiction\nSound knowledge regarding NRSR Act and Railway Safety Standards (ISO/SABS)\nExcellent knowledge of regional railway operators/industry\nProject Management Principles and Approaches\n \nKEY RESULTS AREAS\nSwift response to railway occurrences when instructed to do so by the Principal Inspector or Regional Technical Manager.\nConduct railway safety audits and inspections as per the regional operational plan and in line with the RSR Compliance policies and procedures.\nDocument all audit and inspection findings, including recommendations in line with the RSR Compliance policies and procedures.\nEnforcement of compliance where non-compliances are detected in line with the NRSR Act and RSR Policies and procedures.\nSubmit accurate and complete reports to the Principal Inspector for approval.\nFollow through on all audits and inspection reports to ensure the appropriate and timely closure thereof.\nConduct site visits and inspections to ensure that the recommendations and/or non-compliances have been implemented by operators.\nEnsure that recommendations are correctly and accurately implemented to the extent that the identified risks are adequately mitigated.\nPromotion of railway safety compliance and awareness with all railway operators within the region.\n \nCLOSING DATE: 24 November 2023\n\nIf you are interested in applying for the above-mentioned positions, and for further details of the positions, please visit the RSR recruitment portal https://rsr.mcidirecthire.com/external/currentopportunities\nApplications must be supported by a motivational / application letter, comprehensive curriculum vitae, certified copies of qualifications and a certified copy of your identity document.\nApplications which do not comply with the abovementioned requirements, as well as those received late, will not be considered.\nThe RSR reserves the right to do vetting of references, credentials, criminal records (where applicable) and work experience of any candidate.\nONLY candidates with the qualifying criteria will have an opportunity to be screened and shortlisted for the process.\nThe shortlisted candidates must be willing to complete a competency assessment and medical assessment for inspectors in light of the inherent requirements of the job\nCorrespondence will be limited to shortlisted candidates only.\nIf you have not been contacted within a period of eight (8) weeks after the closing date of this advertisement, please accept that your application has been unsuccessful.\nIn line with the Employment Equity Plan of the Railway Safety Regulator, preference will be given to suitable candidates from the designated groups where applicable.\nThe RSR reserves the right not to fill any advertised position.\nThe processing of your personal information by the Railway Safety Regulator will be done in accordance with the POPI Act 4 of 2013.\nENQUIRIES: Please direct queries to Recruitment@rsr.org.za\n \nWork Level: Management\nJob Type: Permanent\nSalary: Market Related\nEE Position: No\nLocation: Durban Central\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE",
                "TECHNICAL SPECIALIST (MIDRAND)\nReference Number: RSR-47\n \nDescription\nTo define and enforce the requirements for the safety management through all the life cycle phases (concept, design, construction/manufacturing, testing/commissioning, operations & maintenance, modification, decommissioning, and disposal) and conduct research to ensure sustainable and safe railway systems for the country. \n \nREQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS AND EXPERIENCE\nBachelor\u2019s degree in Civil Engineering or equivalent qualification. NQF 7.\nRegistered Professional Engineer /Technologist with ECSA. \n5 years\u2019 experience in the railway engineering industry or operations environment.\n \nTHE FOLLOWING WILL PROVIDE FOR AN ADDED ADVANTAGE:\nQualification in Electrical Engineering\nExcellent knowledge of railway in Telecoms (Passenger Information Systems) and Perway, Structures and Stations\nIn-depth knowledge of  Telecoms and Electrical Engineering technologies and Perway, Structures and Stations\n \nKNOWLEDGE AND EXPERTISE\nExcellent knowledge of railway in Permanent Way /civil/structures (including stations). \nExcellent knowledge of railway operators/industry. \nSound knowledge of railway operations. \nIn-depth knowledge of Perway and Civil Engineering technologies. \nSound knowledge of relevant railway legislation and government policies relating to the rail industry.\nKnowledge of auditing systems, risk management and rail safety management systems. \nExpertise in safety legislation and standards (ISO/SABS). \nSound knowledge of relevant railway legislation and government policies relating to the rail industry. \nIn-depth knowledge of the SANS 3000 series of standards. \nKnowledge on how to identify and formulate the root cause of incidences. \nWorking knowledge of Communication and Negotiations. \n \nKEY RESULTS AREAS\nResearch and investigate discipline related engineering problems associated with rail and recommend solutions.\nConduct benchmarking on industry technologies employees to better understand the future direction of technology.\nResearch current discipline related practices in the railway industry.\nValidate the various technologies against national and international Standards and specifications.\nDraw up reports with findings and recommendations.\nProvide technical inputs to the amendments of standards and guidance documents as required in accordance with SABS legislations and RSR standards.\nProvide input in the development of the draft technical manual requirements when requested.\nConduct discipline specific reviews of new technologies and rail works submitted by railway operators.\nConduct site inspections for new works and new technology development.\nConduct discipline specific technical studies if necessary, in order to provide advice.\nConduct investigations and /or inspections to understand the issue.\nConduct safety audits, inspections and investigations in order to support required RSR initiatives.\nDischarge the powers of the inspector in terms of the act.\nProvide discipline specific technical input to Legal Services for the drafting of regulations.\nInitiate discipline specific technical requirements for the drafting of regulations.\nParticipating in joint interventions with key internal (operations and investigations) and external (operator specialists, Department of Labour, and inspectors) interfaces.\nMaintaining a productive and cooperative working relationship within the industry through the ongoing promoting, monitoring and enforcing of safety. \nParticipate on the State of Safety Report engagements.\n \n \nCLOSING DATE: 24 November 2023\n \nIf you are interested in applying for the above-mentioned positions, and for further details of the positions, please visit the RSR recruitment portal https://rsr.mcidirecthire.com/external/currentopportunities\nApplications must be supported by a motivational / application letter, comprehensive curriculum vitae, certified copies of qualifications and a certified copy of your identity document.\nApplications which do not comply with the abovementioned requirements, as well as those received late, will not be considered.\nThe RSR reserves the right to do vetting of references, credentials, criminal records (where applicable) and work experience of any candidate.\nONLY candidates with the qualifying criteria will have an opportunity to be screened and shortlisted for the process.\nThe shortlisted candidates must be willing to complete a competency assessment and medical assessment for inspectors in light of the inherent requirements of the job\nCorrespondence will be limited to shortlisted candidates only.\nIf you have not been contacted within a period of eight (8) weeks after the closing date of this advertisement, please accept that your application has been unsuccessful.\nIn line with the Employment Equity Plan of the Railway Safety Regulator, preference will be given to suitable candidates from the designated groups where applicable.\nThe RSR reserves the right not to fill any advertised position.\nThe processing of your personal information by the Railway Safety Regulator will be done in accordance with the POPI Act 4 of 2013.\nENQUIRIES: Please direct queries to Recruitment@rsr.org.za\n \nWork Level: Management\nJob Type: Permanent\nSalary: Market Related\nEE Position: No\nLocation: Midrand\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE"
