                " \nROBBEN ISLAND MUSEUM\nNelson Mandela Gateway to Robben Island\nClock tower V&A Waterfront Cape Town 8000 South Africa\nPO Box 51806 V&A Waterfront Cape Town 8002 South Africa\nT +27 21 413 4200 | F +27 21 419 1057\nwww.robben-island.org.za\n ",
                "PROJECT MANAGER \nTOTAL COST TO COMPANY: R 589 117.11 - R824 763.96 \nGRADE: P6 \n6 Months Contract \nThe above-mentioned position is available in the Heritage Department at Robben Island Museum. The purpose of the job of the Project Manager is to oversee projects from start to finish, communicate with stakeholders regarding the status of the project and supervise staff and ensure successful completion of projects on time. \n \nDuties and Responsibilities: \n\uf0b7 Identifying project goals, needs and scope \n\uf0b7 Planning, monitoring and documenting tasks throughout a project \n\uf0b7 Ensuring all tasks, deliverables, and project materials are delivered promptly \n\uf0b7 Managing all resources necessary for project execution \n\uf0b7 Fostering effective communication with stakeholders concerning project status \n\uf0b7 Foreseeing and strategically eliminating blockers and potential risks \n\uf0b7 Documenting each step of the process using various project management tools \n\n\uf0b7 Ensuring top quality results and success for a project \n\uf0b7 Lead and manage the team \n\uf0b7 Ensure stakeholder satisfaction \n\uf0b7 Evaluate project performance \n\uf0b7 Manage project risks, including the development of contingency plans \n\uf0b7 Applying change control and configuration management processes \n\uf0b7 Reporting through agreed lines on project progress \n\uf0b7 Adopting and applying appropriate technical and quality strategies and standards \n\uf0b7 Managing project administration \n \nMinimum Qualification Requirements \n\uf0b7 Post graduate Diploma in Project Management or equivalent (NQF 8). \n \nWork Experience: \n\uf0b7 Minimum 5 years\u2019 experience in coordinating and managing complex event projects, either in the private or public sector, using an established project management methodology of which at least 3 years\u2019 experience must be at management level. \n \nRequired Skills, Competencies and Attributes: \n\uf0b7 Management and leadership skills \n\uf0b7 Computer literacy \n\uf0b7 Problem solving and analytical skills \n\uf0b7 Report writing skills \n\uf0b7 Ability to be an innovative leader \n\uf0b7 Facilitation skills \n\uf0b7 Valid driver\u2019s license \n\uf0b7 Decision making \n\uf0b7 Financial Management \n\uf0b7 Organization and Time management \n\uf0b7 Motivation and Team management \n\uf0b7 Communication skills \n\uf0b7 Negotiation skills \n\uf0b7 Planning skills",
